### =====================================================================
### REST Client requests for docker-nestjs-learning
###
### Requires the "REST Client" VS Code extension (humao.rest-client).
### Send a request by clicking the "Send Request" codelens above each
### block, or with Ctrl+Alt+R (Cmd+Alt+R on macOS).
###
### The api-gateway is the only externally-exposed service. Everything
### else (users-service TCP, postgres, redis) is internal to the compose
### network. Default host port is 3000 (override via API_PORT in .env).
### =====================================================================

@host = http://localhost:3000
@contentType = application/json

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Health — liveness. Should always return { status: "ok" } as long as
### the Nest process is up. Safe for K8s livenessProbe.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/livez

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Health — readiness. Pings users-service (TCP) + redis. Returns 503
### if any downstream is down. Safe for K8s readinessProbe.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/readyz

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — create. Forwards to users-service over TCP, which persists
### to postgres via TypeORM. Response is the created UserDto (with id).
### The `@name createUser` lets later requests reuse the returned id.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
# @name createUser
POST {{host}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Ada1 Lovelace",
  "email": "ada1@example.com"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — list all.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/users

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — find one by id. Uses the id returned from the createUser
### request above. Send `createUser` first, then this one.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/users/{{createUser.response.body.id}}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — find one by explicit id (edit as needed).
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
GET {{host}}/users/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — validation failure example. `name` is too short and `email`
### is not a valid email → global ValidationPipe returns 400 with the
### class-validator error messages.
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "A",
  "email": "not-an-email"
}

### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
### Users — forbidNonWhitelisted example. Extra properties (`role`)
### are rejected by the ValidationPipe (whitelist + forbidNonWhitelisted).
### ---------------------------------------------------------------------
POST {{host}}/users
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "name": "Grace Hopper",
  "email": "grace@example.com",
  "role": "admin"
}
